240static void
241eom_window_set_collection_mode (EomWindow *window, EomWindowCollectionPos position, gboolean resizable)
242{
243 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
244 GtkWidget *hpaned;
245 EomThumbNavMode mode = EOM_THUMB_NAV_MODE_ONE_ROW;
246
247 eom_debug (DEBUG_PREFERENCES);
248
249 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (window));
250
251 priv = window->priv;
252
253 if (priv->collection_position == position &&
254 priv->collection_resizable == resizable)
255 return;
256
257 priv->collection_position = position;
258 priv->collection_resizable = resizable;
259
260 hpaned = gtk_widget_get_parent (priv->sidebar);
261
262 g_object_ref (hpaned);
263 g_object_ref (priv->nav);
264
265 gtk_container_remove (GTK_CONTAINER (priv->layout), hpaned);
266 gtk_container_remove (GTK_CONTAINER (priv->layout), priv->nav);
267
268 gtk_widget_destroy (priv->layout);
269
270 switch (position) {
271 case EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_BOTTOM:
272 case EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_TOP:
273 if (resizable) {
274 mode = EOM_THUMB_NAV_MODE_MULTIPLE_ROWS;
275
276 priv->layout = gtk_paned_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_VERTICAL);
277
278 if (position == EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_BOTTOM) {
279 gtk_paned_pack1 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, FALSE);
280 gtk_paned_pack2 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, TRUE);
281 } else {
282 gtk_paned_pack1 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, TRUE);
283 gtk_paned_pack2 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, FALSE);
284 }
285 } else {
286 mode = EOM_THUMB_NAV_MODE_ONE_ROW;
287
288 priv->layout = gtk_box_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_VERTICAL, 2);
289
290 if (position == EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_BOTTOM) {
291 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
292 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
293 } else {
294 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
295 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
296 }
297 }
298 break;
299
300 case EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_LEFT:
301 case EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_RIGHT:
302 if (resizable) {
303 mode = EOM_THUMB_NAV_MODE_MULTIPLE_COLUMNS;
304
305 priv->layout = gtk_paned_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_HORIZONTAL);
306
307 if (position == EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_LEFT) {
308 gtk_paned_pack1 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, TRUE);
309 gtk_paned_pack2 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, FALSE);
310 } else {
311 gtk_paned_pack1 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, FALSE);
312 gtk_paned_pack2 (GTK_PANED (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, TRUE);
313 }
314 } else {
315 mode = EOM_THUMB_NAV_MODE_ONE_COLUMN;
316
317 priv->layout = gtk_box_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_HORIZONTAL, 2);
318
319 if (position == EOM_WINDOW_COLLECTION_POS_LEFT) {
320 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
321 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
322 } else {
323 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), hpaned, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
324 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (priv->layout), priv->nav, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
325 }
326 }
327
328 break;
329 }
330
331 gtk_box_pack_end (GTK_BOX (priv->cbox), priv->layout, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
332
333 eom_thumb_nav_set_mode (EOM_THUMB_NAV (priv->nav), mode);
334
335 if (priv->mode != EOM_WINDOW_MODE_UNKNOWN) {
336 update_action_groups_state (window);
337 }
338}

340static void
341eom_window_can_save_changed_cb (GSettings *settings, gchar *key, gpointer user_data)
342{
343 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
344 EomWindow *window;
345 gboolean save_disabled = FALSE;
346 GtkAction *action_save, *action_save_as;
347
348 eom_debug (DEBUG_PREFERENCES);
349
350 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (user_data));
351
352 window = EOM_WINDOW (user_data);
353 priv = EOM_WINDOW (user_data)->priv;
354
355 save_disabled = g_settings_get_boolean (settings, key);
356
357 priv->save_disabled = save_disabled;
358
359 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
360 action_save =
361 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image, "ImageSave");
362 action_save_as =
363 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image, "ImageSaveAs");
364
365 if (priv->save_disabled) {
366 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_save, FALSE);
367 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_save_as, FALSE);
368 } else {
369 EomImage *image = eom_window_get_image (window);
370
371 if (EOM_IS_IMAGE (image)) {
372 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_save,
373 eom_image_is_modified (image));
374
375 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_save_as, TRUE);
376 }
377 }
378 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
379}

381#if defined(HAVE_LCMS) && defined(GDK_WINDOWING_X11)
382static cmsHPROFILE *
383eom_window_get_display_profile (GdkScreen *screen)
384{
385 Display *dpy;
386 Atom icc_atom, type;
387 int format;
388 gulong nitems;
389 gulong bytes_after;
390 gulong length;
391 guchar *str;
392 int result;
393 cmsHPROFILE *profile = NULL;
394 char *atom_name;
395
396 if (!GDK_IS_X11_SCREEN (screen)) {
397 return NULL;
398 }
399
400 dpy = GDK_DISPLAY_XDISPLAY (gdk_screen_get_display (screen));
401
402 if (gdk_x11_screen_get_screen_number (screen) > 0)
403 atom_name = g_strdup_printf ("_ICC_PROFILE_%d", gdk_x11_screen_get_screen_number (screen));
404 else
405 atom_name = g_strdup ("_ICC_PROFILE");
406
407 icc_atom = gdk_x11_get_xatom_by_name_for_display (gdk_screen_get_display (screen), atom_name);
408
409 g_free (atom_name);
410
411 result = XGetWindowProperty (dpy,
412 GDK_WINDOW_XID (gdk_screen_get_root_window (screen)),
413 icc_atom,
414 0,
415 G_MAXLONG,
416 False,
417 XA_CARDINAL,
418 &type,
419 &format,
420 &nitems,
421 &bytes_after,
422 (guchar **)&str);
423
424 /* TODO: handle bytes_after != 0 */
425
426 if ((result == Success) && (type == XA_CARDINAL) && (nitems > 0)) {
427 switch (format)
428 {
429 case 8:
430 length = nitems;
431 break;
432 case 16:
433 length = sizeof(short) * nitems;
434 break;
435 case 32:
436 length = sizeof(long) * nitems;
437 break;
438 default:
439 eom_debug_message (DEBUG_LCMS, "Unable to read profile, not correcting");
440
441 XFree (str);
442 return NULL;
443 }
444
445 profile = cmsOpenProfileFromMem (str, length);
446
447 if (G_UNLIKELY (profile == NULL)) {
448 eom_debug_message (DEBUG_LCMS,
449 "Invalid display profile set, "
450 "not using it");
451 }
452
453 XFree (str);
454 }
455
456 if (profile == NULL) {
457 profile = cmsCreate_sRGBProfile ();
458 eom_debug_message (DEBUG_LCMS,
459 "No valid display profile set, assuming sRGB");
460 }
461
462 return profile;
463}
464#endif

466static void
467update_image_pos (EomWindow *window)
468{
469 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
470 gint pos = -1, n_images = 0;
471
472 priv = window->priv;
473
474 n_images = eom_list_store_length (EOM_LIST_STORE (priv->store));
475
476 if (n_images > 0) {
477 pos = eom_list_store_get_pos_by_image (EOM_LIST_STORE (priv->store),
478 priv->image);
479 }
480 /* Images: (image pos) / (n_total_images) */
481 eom_statusbar_set_image_number (EOM_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
482 pos + 1,
483 n_images);
484
485}
486
487static void
488update_status_bar (EomWindow *window)
489{
490 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
491 char *str = NULL;
492
493 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (window));
494
495 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
496
497 priv = window->priv;
498
499 if (priv->image != NULL)
500 {
501 if ( eom_image_has_data (priv->image, EOM_IMAGE_DATA_DIMENSION))
502 {
503 int zoom, width, height;
504 goffset bytes = 0;
505
506 zoom = floor (100 * eom_scroll_view_get_zoom (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (priv->view)) + 0.5);
507
508 eom_image_get_size (priv->image, &width, &height);
509
510 bytes = eom_image_get_bytes (priv->image);
511
512 if ((width > 0) && (height > 0)) {
513 char *size_string;
514
515 size_string = g_format_size (bytes);
516
517 /* Translators: This is the string displayed in the statusbar
518 * The tokens are from left to right:
519 * - image width
520 * - image height
521 * - image size in bytes
522 * - zoom in percent */
523 str = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("%i %i pixel %s %i%%",
524 "%i %i pixels %s %i%%", height),
525 width,
526 height,
527 size_string,
528 zoom);
529
530 g_free (size_string);
531 }
532 }
533 update_image_pos (window);
534 }
535
536 gtk_statusbar_pop (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
537 priv->image_info_message_cid);
538
539 gtk_statusbar_push (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
540 priv->image_info_message_cid, str ? str : "");
541
542 g_free (str);
543}

545static void
546eom_window_set_message_area (EomWindow *window,
547 GtkWidget *message_area)
548{
549 if (window->priv->message_area == message_area)
550 return;
551
552 if (window->priv->message_area != NULL)
553 gtk_widget_destroy (window->priv->message_area);
554
555 window->priv->message_area = message_area;
556
557 if (message_area == NULL) return;
558
559 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (window->priv->cbox),
560 window->priv->message_area,
561 FALSE,
562 FALSE,
563 0);
564
565 g_object_add_weak_pointer (G_OBJECT (window->priv->message_area),
566 (void *) &window->priv->message_area);
567}

569static void
570update_action_groups_state (EomWindow *window)
571{
572 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
573 GtkAction *action_collection;
574 GtkAction *action_sidebar;
575 GtkAction *action_fscreen;
576 GtkAction *action_sshow;
577 GtkAction *action_print;
578 gboolean print_disabled = FALSE;
579 gint n_images = 0;
580
581 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (window));
582
583 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
584
585 priv = window->priv;
586
587 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
588 action_collection =
589 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_window,
590 "ViewImageCollection");
591
592 action_sidebar =
593 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_window,
594 "ViewSidebar");
595
596 action_fscreen =
597 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image,
598 "ViewFullscreen");
599
600 action_sshow =
601 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_collection,
602 "ViewSlideshow");
603
604 action_print =
605 gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image,
606 "ImagePrint");
607 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
608
609 g_assert (action_collection != NULL);
610 g_assert (action_sidebar != NULL);
611 g_assert (action_fscreen != NULL);
612 g_assert (action_sshow != NULL);
613 g_assert (action_print != NULL);
614
615 if (priv->store != NULL) {
616 n_images = eom_list_store_length (EOM_LIST_STORE (priv->store));
617 }
618
619 if (n_images == 0) {
620 gtk_widget_hide (priv->layout);
621
622 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
623 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_window, TRUE);
624 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_image, FALSE);
625 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_collection, FALSE);
626
627 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_fscreen, FALSE);
628 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_sshow, FALSE);
629 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
630
631 /* If there are no images on model, initialization
632 stops here. */
633 if (priv->status == EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_INIT) {
634 priv->status = EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_NORMAL;
635 }
636 } else {
637 gboolean show_image_collection;
638
639 if (priv->flags & EOM_STARTUP_DISABLE_COLLECTION) {
640 g_settings_set_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_IMAGE_COLLECTION, FALSE);
641
642 show_image_collection = FALSE;
643 } else {
644 show_image_collection =
645 g_settings_get_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_IMAGE_COLLECTION);
646 }
647
648 show_image_collection = show_image_collection &&
649 n_images > 1 &&
650 priv->mode != EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW;
651
652 gtk_widget_show (priv->layout);
653
654 if (show_image_collection)
655 gtk_widget_show (priv->nav);
656
657 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
658 gtk_toggle_action_set_active (GTK_TOGGLE_ACTION (action_collection),
659 show_image_collection);
660
661 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_window, TRUE);
662 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_image, TRUE);
663
664 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_fscreen, TRUE);
665
666 if (n_images == 1) {
667 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_collection, FALSE);
668 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_collection, FALSE);
669 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_sshow, FALSE);
670 } else {
671 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_collection, TRUE);
672 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_sshow, TRUE);
673 }
674 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
675
676 if (show_image_collection)
677 gtk_widget_grab_focus (priv->thumbview);
678 else
679 gtk_widget_grab_focus (priv->view);
680 }
681
682 print_disabled = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->lockdown_settings,
683 EOM_CONF_LOCKDOWN_CAN_PRINT);
684
685 if (print_disabled) {
686 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
687 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_print, FALSE);
688 }
689
690 if (eom_sidebar_is_empty (EOM_SIDEBAR (priv->sidebar))) {
691 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_sidebar, FALSE);
692 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
693 gtk_widget_hide (priv->sidebar);
694 }

721static gboolean
722add_file_to_recent_files (GFile *file)
723{
724 gchar *text_uri;
725 GFileInfo *file_info;
726 GtkRecentData *recent_data;
727 static gchar *groups[2] = { EOM_RECENT_FILES_GROUP , NULL };
728
729 if (file == NULL) return FALSE;
730
731 /* The password gets stripped here because ~/.recently-used.xbel is
732 * readable by everyone (chmod 644). It also makes the workaround
733 * for the bug with gtk_recent_info_get_uri_display() easier
734 * (see the comment in eom_window_update_recent_files_menu()). */
735 text_uri = g_file_get_uri (file);
736
737 if (text_uri == NULL)
738 return FALSE;
739
740 file_info = g_file_query_info (file,
741 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_CONTENT_TYPE","
742 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_FAST_CONTENT_TYPE,
743 0, NULL, NULL);
744 if (file_info == NULL)
745 return FALSE;
746
747 recent_data = g_slice_new (GtkRecentData);
748 recent_data->display_name = NULL;
749 recent_data->description = NULL;
750 recent_data->mime_type = (gchar *) eom_util_get_content_type_with_fallback (file_info);
751 recent_data->app_name = EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME;
752 recent_data->app_exec = g_strjoin(" ", g_get_prgname (), "%u", NULL);
753 recent_data->groups = groups;
754 recent_data->is_private = FALSE;
755
756 gtk_recent_manager_add_full (gtk_recent_manager_get_default (),
757 text_uri,
758 recent_data);
759
760 g_free (recent_data->app_exec);
761 g_free (text_uri);
762 g_object_unref (file_info);
763
764 g_slice_free (GtkRecentData, recent_data);
765
766 return FALSE;
767}

816static void
817image_file_changed_cb (EomImage *img, EomWindow *window)
818{
819 GtkWidget *info_bar;
820 gchar *text, *markup;
821 GtkWidget *image;
822 GtkWidget *label;
823 GtkWidget *hbox;
824
825 if (window->priv->needs_reload_confirmation == FALSE)
826 return;
827
828 if (!eom_image_is_modified (img)) {
829 /* Auto-reload when image is unmodified */
830 eom_window_reload_image (window);
831 return;
832 }
833
834 window->priv->needs_reload_confirmation = FALSE;
835
836 info_bar = gtk_info_bar_new_with_buttons (_("_Reload"),
837 GTK_RESPONSE_YES,
838 C_("MessageArea", "Hi_de"),
839 GTK_RESPONSE_NO, NULL);
840 gtk_info_bar_set_message_type (GTK_INFO_BAR (info_bar),
841 GTK_MESSAGE_QUESTION);
842 image = gtk_image_new_from_icon_name ("dialog-question",
843 GTK_ICON_SIZE_DIALOG);
844 label = gtk_label_new (NULL);
845
846 /* The newline character is currently necessary due to a problem
847 * with the automatic line break. */
848 text = g_strdup_printf (_("The image \"%s\" has been modified by an external application."
849 "\nWould you like to reload it?"), eom_image_get_caption (img));
850 markup = g_markup_printf_escaped ("<b>%s</b>", text);
851 gtk_label_set_markup (GTK_LABEL (label), markup);
852 g_free (text);
853 g_free (markup);
854
855 hbox = gtk_box_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_HORIZONTAL, 8);
856 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (hbox), image, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
857 gtk_widget_set_halign (image, GTK_ALIGN_START);
858 gtk_widget_set_valign (image, GTK_ALIGN_END);
859 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (hbox), label, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
860 gtk_label_set_xalign (GTK_LABEL (label), 0.0);
861 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (gtk_info_bar_get_content_area (GTK_INFO_BAR (info_bar))), hbox, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
862 gtk_widget_show_all (hbox);
863 gtk_widget_show (info_bar);
864
865 eom_window_set_message_area (window, info_bar);
866 g_signal_connect (info_bar, "response",
867 G_CALLBACK (file_changed_info_bar_response),
868 window);
869}

934static void
935eom_window_update_openwith_menu (EomWindow *window, EomImage *image)
936{
937 gboolean edit_button_active;
938 GAppInfo *editor_app;
939 GFile *file;
940 GFileInfo *file_info;
941 GList *iter;
942 gchar *label, *tip;
943 const gchar *mime_type;
944 GtkAction *action;
945 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
946 GList *apps;
947 guint action_id = 0;
948 GIcon *app_icon;
949 char *path;
950 GtkWidget *menuitem;
951
952 priv = window->priv;
953
954 edit_button_active = FALSE;
955 editor_app = get_appinfo_for_editor (window);
956
957 file = eom_image_get_file (image);
958 file_info = g_file_query_info (file,
959 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_CONTENT_TYPE","
960 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_FAST_CONTENT_TYPE,
961 0, NULL, NULL);
962
963 if (file_info == NULL)
964 return;
965 else {
966 mime_type = eom_util_get_content_type_with_fallback (file_info);
967 }
968
969 if (priv->open_with_menu_id != 0) {
970 gtk_ui_manager_remove_ui (priv->ui_mgr, priv->open_with_menu_id);
971 priv->open_with_menu_id = 0;
972 }
973
974 if (priv->actions_open_with != NULL) {
975 gtk_ui_manager_remove_action_group (priv->ui_mgr, priv->actions_open_with);
976 g_object_unref (priv->actions_open_with);
977 priv->actions_open_with = NULL;
978 }
979
980 if (mime_type == NULL) {
981 g_object_unref (file_info);
982 return;
983 }
984
985 apps = g_app_info_get_all_for_type (mime_type);
986
987 g_object_unref (file_info);
988
989 if (!apps)
990 return;
991
992 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
993 priv->actions_open_with = gtk_action_group_new ("OpenWithActions");
994 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
995 gtk_ui_manager_insert_action_group (priv->ui_mgr, priv->actions_open_with, -1);
996
997 priv->open_with_menu_id = gtk_ui_manager_new_merge_id (priv->ui_mgr);
998
999 for (iter = apps; iter; iter = iter->next) {
1000 GAppInfo *app = iter->data;
1001 gchar name[64];
1002
1003 if (editor_app != NULL && g_app_info_equal (editor_app, app)) {
1004 edit_button_active = TRUE;
1005 }
1006
1007 /* Do not include eom itself */
1008 if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (g_app_info_get_executable (app),
1009 g_get_prgname ()) == 0) {
1010 g_object_unref (app);
1011 continue;
1012 }
1013
1014 g_snprintf (name, sizeof (name), "OpenWith%u", action_id++);
1015
1016 label = g_strdup (g_app_info_get_name (app));
1017 tip = g_strdup_printf (_("Use \"%s\" to open the selected image"), g_app_info_get_name (app));
1018
1019 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1020 action = gtk_action_new (name, label, tip, NULL);
1021 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1022
1023 app_icon = g_app_info_get_icon (app);
1024 if (G_LIKELY (app_icon != NULL)) {
1025 g_object_ref (app_icon);
1026 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1027 gtk_action_set_gicon (action, app_icon);
1028 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1029 g_object_unref (app_icon);
1030 }
1031
1032 g_free (label);
1033 g_free (tip);
1034
1035 g_object_set_data_full (G_OBJECT (action), "app", app,
1036 (GDestroyNotify) g_object_unref);
1037
1038 g_signal_connect (action, "activate",
1039 G_CALLBACK (open_with_launch_application_cb),
1040 image);
1041
1042 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1043 gtk_action_group_add_action (priv->actions_open_with, action);
1044 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1045 g_object_unref (action);
1046
1047 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (priv->ui_mgr,
1048 priv->open_with_menu_id,
1049 "/MainMenu/Image/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder",
1050 name,
1051 name,
1052 GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENUITEM,
1053 FALSE);
1054
1055 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (priv->ui_mgr,
1056 priv->open_with_menu_id,
1057 "/ThumbnailPopup/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder",
1058 name,
1059 name,
1060 GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENUITEM,
1061 FALSE);
1062 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (priv->ui_mgr,
1063 priv->open_with_menu_id,
1064 "/ViewPopup/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder",
1065 name,
1066 name,
1067 GTK_UI_MANAGER_MENUITEM,
1068 FALSE);
1069
1070 path = g_strdup_printf ("/MainMenu/Image/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder/%s", name);
1071
1072 menuitem = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (priv->ui_mgr, path);
1073
1074 /* Only force displaying the icon if it is an application icon */
1075 gtk_image_menu_item_set_always_show_image (GTK_IMAGE_MENU_ITEM (menuitem), app_icon != NULL);
1076
1077 g_free (path);
1078
1079 path = g_strdup_printf ("/ThumbnailPopup/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder/%s", name);
1080
1081 menuitem = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (priv->ui_mgr, path);
1082
1083 /* Only force displaying the icon if it is an application icon */
1084 gtk_image_menu_item_set_always_show_image (GTK_IMAGE_MENU_ITEM (menuitem), app_icon != NULL);
1085
1086 g_free (path);
1087
1088 path = g_strdup_printf ("/ViewPopup/ImageOpenWith/Applications Placeholder/%s", name);
1089
1090 menuitem = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (priv->ui_mgr, path);
1091
1092 /* Only force displaying the icon if it is an application icon */
1093 gtk_image_menu_item_set_always_show_image (GTK_IMAGE_MENU_ITEM (menuitem), app_icon != NULL);
1094
1095 g_free (path);
1096 }
1097
1098 g_list_free (apps);
1099
1100 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1101 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (window->priv->actions_image,
1102 "OpenEditor");
1103 if (action != NULL) {
1104 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action, edit_button_active);
1105 }
1106 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1107}

1149static void
1150eom_job_save_progress_cb (EomJobSave *job, float progress, gpointer user_data)
1151{
1152 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
1153 EomWindow *window;
1154
1155 static EomImage *image = NULL;
1156
1157 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (user_data));
1158
1159 window = EOM_WINDOW (user_data);
1160 priv = window->priv;
1161
1162 eom_statusbar_set_progress (EOM_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1163 progress);
1164
1165 if (image != job->current_image) {
1166 gchar *str_image, *status_message;
1167 guint n_images;
1168
1169 image = job->current_image;
1170
1171 n_images = g_list_length (job->images);
1172
1173 str_image = eom_image_get_uri_for_display (image);
1174
1175 /* Translators: This string is displayed in the statusbar
1176 * while saving images. The tokens are from left to right:
1177 * - the original filename
1178 * - the current image's position in the queue
1179 * - the total number of images queued for saving */
1180 status_message = g_strdup_printf (_("Saving image \"%s\" (%u/%u)"),
1181 str_image,
1182 job->current_pos + 1,
1183 n_images);
1184 g_free (str_image);
1185
1186 gtk_statusbar_pop (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1187 priv->image_info_message_cid);
1188
1189 gtk_statusbar_push (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1190 priv->image_info_message_cid,
1191 status_message);
1192
1193 g_free (status_message);
1194 }
1195
1196 if (progress == 1.0)
1197 image = NULL;
1198}

1200static void
1201eom_window_obtain_desired_size (EomImage *image,
1202 gint width,
1203 gint height,
1204 EomWindow *window)
1205{
1206 GdkScreen *screen;
1207 GdkDisplay *display;
1208 GdkRectangle monitor;
1209 GtkAllocation allocation;
1210 gint final_width, final_height;
1211 gint screen_width, screen_height;
1212 gint window_width, window_height;
1213 gint img_width, img_height;
1214 gint view_width, view_height;
1215 gint deco_width, deco_height;
1216
1217 update_action_groups_state (window);
1218
1219 img_width = width;
1220 img_height = height;
1221
1222 if (!gtk_widget_get_realized (window->priv->view)) {
1223 gtk_widget_realize (window->priv->view);
1224 }
1225
1226 gtk_widget_get_allocation (window->priv->view, &allocation);
1227 view_width = allocation.width;
1228 view_height = allocation.height;
1229
1230 if (!gtk_widget_get_realized (GTK_WIDGET (window))) {
1231 gtk_widget_realize (GTK_WIDGET (window));
1232 }
1233
1234 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (window), &allocation);
1235 window_width = allocation.width;
1236 window_height = allocation.height;
1237
1238 screen = gtk_window_get_screen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
1239 display = gdk_screen_get_display (screen);
1240
1241 gdk_monitor_get_geometry (gdk_display_get_monitor_at_window (display,
1242 gtk_widget_get_window (GTK_WIDGET (window))),
1243 &monitor);
1244
1245 screen_width = monitor.width;
1246 screen_height = monitor.height;
1247
1248 deco_width = window_width - view_width;
1249 deco_height = window_height - view_height;
1250
1251 if (img_width > 0 && img_height > 0) {
1252 if ((img_width + deco_width > screen_width) ||
1253 (img_height + deco_height > screen_height))
1254 {
1255 double factor;
1256
1257 if (img_width > img_height) {
1258 factor = (screen_width * 0.75 - deco_width) / (double) img_width;
1259 } else {
1260 factor = (screen_height * 0.75 - deco_height) / (double) img_height;
1261 }
1262
1263 img_width = img_width * factor;
1264 img_height = img_height * factor;
1265 }
1266 }
1267
1268 final_width = MAX (EOM_WINDOW_MIN_WIDTH, img_width + deco_width);
1269 final_height = MAX (EOM_WINDOW_MIN_HEIGHT, img_height + deco_height);
1270
1271 eom_debug_message (DEBUG_WINDOW, "Setting window size: %d x %d", final_width, final_height);
1272
1273 gtk_window_set_default_size (GTK_WINDOW (window), final_width, final_height);
1274
1275 g_signal_emit (window, signals[SIGNAL_PREPARED], 0);
1276}

1294static void
1295eom_job_load_cb (EomJobLoad *job, gpointer data)
1296{
1297 EomWindow *window;
1298 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
1299 GtkAction *action_undo, *action_save;
1300
1301 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (data));
1302
1303 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
1304
1305 window = EOM_WINDOW (data);
1306 priv = window->priv;
1307
1308 eom_statusbar_set_progress (EOM_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar), 0.0);
1309
1310 gtk_statusbar_pop (GTK_STATUSBAR (window->priv->statusbar),
1311 priv->image_info_message_cid);
1312
1313 if (priv->image != NULL) {
1314 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (priv->image,
1315 image_thumb_changed_cb,
1316 window);
1317 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (priv->image,
1318 image_file_changed_cb,
1319 window);
1320
1321 g_object_unref (priv->image);
1322 }
1323
1324 priv->image = g_object_ref (job->image);
1325
1326 if (EOM_JOB (job)->error == NULL) {
1327#if defined(HAVE_LCMS) && defined(GDK_WINDOWING_X11)
1328 eom_image_apply_display_profile (job->image,
1329 priv->display_profile);
1330#endif
1331
1332 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1333 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_image, TRUE);
1334 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1335
1336 eom_window_display_image (window, job->image);
1337 } else {
1338 GtkWidget *message_area;
1339
1340 message_area = eom_image_load_error_message_area_new (
1341 eom_image_get_caption (job->image),
1342 EOM_JOB (job)->error);
1343
1344 g_signal_connect (message_area, "response",
1345 G_CALLBACK (eom_window_error_message_area_response),
1346 window);
1347
1348 gtk_window_set_icon (GTK_WINDOW (window), NULL);
1349 gtk_window_set_title (GTK_WINDOW (window),
1350 eom_image_get_caption (job->image));
1351
1352 eom_window_set_message_area (window, message_area);
1353
1354 gtk_info_bar_set_default_response (GTK_INFO_BAR (message_area),
1355 GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL);
1356
1357 gtk_widget_show (message_area);
1358
1359 update_status_bar (window);
1360
1361 eom_scroll_view_set_image (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (priv->view), NULL);
1362
1363 if (window->priv->status == EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_INIT) {
1364 update_action_groups_state (window);
1365
1366 g_signal_emit (window, signals[SIGNAL_PREPARED], 0);
1367 }
1368
1369 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1370 gtk_action_group_set_sensitive (priv->actions_image, FALSE);
1371 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1372 }
1373
1374 eom_window_clear_load_job (window);
1375
1376 if (window->priv->status == EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_INIT) {
1377 window->priv->status = EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_NORMAL;
1378
1379 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (job->image,
1380 eom_window_obtain_desired_size,
1381 window);
1382 }
1383
1384 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1385 action_save = gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image, "ImageSave");
1386 action_undo = gtk_action_group_get_action (priv->actions_image, "EditUndo");
1387
1388 /* Set Save and Undo sensitive according to image state.
1389 * Respect lockdown in case of Save.*/
1390 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_save, (!priv->save_disabled && eom_image_is_modified (job->image)));
1391 gtk_action_set_sensitive (action_undo, eom_image_is_modified (job->image));
1392 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1393
1394 g_object_unref (job->image);
1395}

1471static void
1472handle_image_selection_changed_cb (EomThumbView *thumbview, EomWindow *window)
1473{
1474 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
1475 EomImage *image;
1476 gchar *status_message;
1477 gchar *str_image;
1478
1479 priv = window->priv;
1480
1481 if (eom_list_store_length (EOM_LIST_STORE (priv->store)) == 0) {
1482 gtk_window_set_title (GTK_WINDOW (window),
1483 g_get_application_name());
1484 gtk_statusbar_remove_all (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1485 priv->image_info_message_cid);
1486 eom_scroll_view_set_image (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (priv->view),
1487 NULL);
1488 }
1489
1490 if (eom_thumb_view_get_n_selected (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview)) == 0)
1491 return;
1492
1493 update_selection_ui_visibility (window);
1494
1495 image = eom_thumb_view_get_first_selected_image (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview));
1496
1497 g_assert (EOM_IS_IMAGE (image));
1498
1499 eom_window_clear_load_job (window);
1500
1501 eom_window_set_message_area (window, NULL);
1502
1503 gtk_statusbar_pop (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1504 priv->image_info_message_cid);
1505
1506 if (image == priv->image) {
1507 update_status_bar (window);
1508 return;
1509 }
1510
1511 if (eom_image_has_data (image, EOM_IMAGE_DATA_IMAGE)) {
1512 if (priv->image != NULL)
1513 g_object_unref (priv->image);
1514
1515 priv->image = image;
1516 eom_window_display_image (window, image);
1517 return;
1518 }
1519
1520 if (priv->status == EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_INIT) {
1521 g_signal_connect (image, "size-prepared",
1522 G_CALLBACK (eom_window_obtain_desired_size),
1523 window);
1524 }
1525
1526 priv->load_job = eom_job_load_new (image, EOM_IMAGE_DATA_ALL);
1527
1528 g_signal_connect (priv->load_job, "finished",
1529 G_CALLBACK (eom_job_load_cb),
1530 window);
1531
1532 g_signal_connect (priv->load_job, "progress",
1533 G_CALLBACK (eom_job_progress_cb),
1534 window);
1535
1536 eom_job_queue_add_job (priv->load_job);
1537
1538 str_image = eom_image_get_uri_for_display (image);
1539
1540 status_message = g_strdup_printf (_("Opening image \"%s\""),
1541 str_image);
1542
1543 g_free (str_image);
1544
1545 gtk_statusbar_push (GTK_STATUSBAR (priv->statusbar),
1546 priv->image_info_message_cid, status_message);
1547
1548 g_free (status_message);
1549}

1690static void

1692{

1694 GdkRectangle screen_rect;
1695 GdkScreen *screen;
1696 GdkDisplay *display;
1697
1698 g_return_if_fail (popup != NULL);
1699
1700 if (gtk_widget_get_window (GTK_WIDGET (window)) == NULL) return;

1707 &screen_rect);
1708
1709 gtk_widget_set_size_request (popup,
1710 screen_rect.width,
1711 -1);
1712
1713 gtk_window_move (GTK_WINDOW (popup), screen_rect.x, screen_rect.y);
1714}

1750static gboolean
1751slideshow_switch_cb (gpointer data)
1752{
1753 EomWindow *window = EOM_WINDOW (data);
1754 EomWindowPrivate *priv = window->priv;
1755
1756 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
1757
1758 if (priv->slideshow_random) {
1759 eom_thumb_view_select_single (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview),
1760 EOM_THUMB_VIEW_SELECT_RANDOM);
1761 return TRUE;
1762 }
1763
1764 if (!priv->slideshow_loop && slideshow_is_loop_end (window)) {
1765 eom_window_stop_fullscreen (window, TRUE);
1766 return FALSE;
1767 }
1768
1769 eom_thumb_view_select_single (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview),
1770 EOM_THUMB_VIEW_SELECT_RIGHT);
1771
1772 return TRUE;
1773}

1789fullscreen_set_timeout (EomWindow *window)
1790{

1920static GtkWidget *
1921eom_window_create_fullscreen_popup (EomWindow *window)
1922{
1923 GtkWidget *popup;
1924 GtkWidget *hbox;
1925 GtkWidget *button;
1926 GtkWidget *toolbar;
1927 GdkScreen *screen;
1928
1929 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
1930
1931 popup = gtk_window_new (GTK_WINDOW_POPUP);
1932
1933 hbox = gtk_box_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_HORIZONTAL, 0);
1934 gtk_container_add (GTK_CONTAINER (popup), hbox);
1935
1936 toolbar = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (window->priv->ui_mgr,
1937 "/FullscreenToolbar");
1938 g_assert (GTK_IS_WIDGET (toolbar));
1939 gtk_toolbar_set_style (GTK_TOOLBAR (toolbar), GTK_TOOLBAR_ICONS);
1940 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (hbox), toolbar, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
1941
1942 button = eom_window_get_exit_fullscreen_button (window);
1943 gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (hbox), button, FALSE, FALSE, 0);
1944
1945 gtk_window_set_resizable (GTK_WINDOW (popup), FALSE);
1946
1947 screen = gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (window));
1948
1949 g_signal_connect_object (screen, "size-changed",
1950 G_CALLBACK (screen_size_changed_cb),
1951 window, 0);
1952
1953 g_signal_connect (popup, "enter-notify-event",
1954 G_CALLBACK (fullscreen_leave_notify_cb),
1955 window);
1956
1957 gtk_window_set_screen (GTK_WINDOW (popup), screen);
1958
1959 return popup;
1960}
1961
1962static void
1963update_ui_visibility (EomWindow *window)
1964{
1965 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
1966
1967 GtkAction *action;
1968 GtkWidget *menubar;
1969
1970 gboolean fullscreen_mode, visible;
1971
1972 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (window));
1973
1974 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
1975
1976 priv = window->priv;
1977
1978 fullscreen_mode = priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN ||
1979 priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW;
1980
1981 menubar = gtk_ui_manager_get_widget (priv->ui_mgr, "/MainMenu");
1982 g_assert (GTK_IS_WIDGET (menubar));
1983
1984 visible = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_TOOLBAR);
1985 visible = visible && !fullscreen_mode;
1986
1987 action = gtk_ui_manager_get_action (priv->ui_mgr, "/MainMenu/View/ToolbarToggle");
1988 g_assert (action != NULL);
1989 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1990 gtk_toggle_action_set_active (GTK_TOGGLE_ACTION (action), visible);
1991 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
1992 g_object_set (G_OBJECT (priv->toolbar), "visible", visible, NULL);
1993
1994 visible = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_STATUSBAR);
1995 visible = visible && !fullscreen_mode;
1996
1997 action = gtk_ui_manager_get_action (priv->ui_mgr, "/MainMenu/View/StatusbarToggle");
1998 g_assert (action != NULL);
1999 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2000 gtk_toggle_action_set_active (GTK_TOGGLE_ACTION (action), visible);
2001 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2002 g_object_set (G_OBJECT (priv->statusbar), "visible", visible, NULL);
2003
2004 if (priv->status != EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_INIT) {
2005 visible = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_IMAGE_COLLECTION);
2006 visible = visible && priv->mode != EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW;
2007 action = gtk_ui_manager_get_action (priv->ui_mgr, "/MainMenu/View/ImageCollectionToggle");
2008 g_assert (action != NULL);
2009 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2010 gtk_toggle_action_set_active (GTK_TOGGLE_ACTION (action), visible);
2011 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2012 if (visible) {
2013 gtk_widget_show (priv->nav);
2014 } else {
2015 gtk_widget_hide (priv->nav);
2016 }
2017 }
2018
2019 visible = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_SIDEBAR);
2020 visible = visible && !fullscreen_mode;
2021 action = gtk_ui_manager_get_action (priv->ui_mgr, "/MainMenu/View/SidebarToggle");
2022 g_assert (action != NULL);

2068static void
2069eom_window_run_fullscreen (EomWindow *window, gboolean slideshow)
2070{
2071 static const GdkRGBA black = { 0., 0., 0., 1.};
2072
2073 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
2074 GtkWidget *menubar;
2075 gboolean upscale;
2076
2077 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
2078
2079 priv = window->priv;
2080
2081 if (slideshow) {
2082 priv->mode = EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW;
2083 } else {
2084 /* Stop the timer if we come from slideshowing */
2085 if (priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW)
2086 slideshow_clear_timeout (window);
2087
2088 priv->mode = EOM_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN;
2089 }
2090
2091 if (window->priv->fullscreen_popup == NULL)
2092 priv->fullscreen_popup

2094
2095 update_ui_visibility (window);

2099 gtk_widget_hide (menubar);
2100
2101 g_signal_connect (priv->view, "motion-notify-event",
2102 G_CALLBACK (fullscreen_motion_notify_cb),
2103 window);
2104
2105 g_signal_connect (priv->view, "leave-notify-event",
2106 G_CALLBACK (fullscreen_leave_notify_cb),
2107 window);
2108
2109 g_signal_connect (priv->thumbview, "motion-notify-event",
2110 G_CALLBACK (fullscreen_motion_notify_cb),
2111 window);
2112
2113 g_signal_connect (priv->thumbview, "leave-notify-event",
2114 G_CALLBACK (fullscreen_leave_notify_cb),
2115 window);
2116
2117 fullscreen_set_timeout (window);
2118
2119 if (slideshow) {
2120 priv->slideshow_random =
2121 g_settings_get_boolean (priv->fullscreen_settings,
2122 EOM_CONF_FULLSCREEN_RANDOM);
2123
2124 priv->slideshow_loop =
2125 g_settings_get_boolean (priv->fullscreen_settings,
2126 EOM_CONF_FULLSCREEN_LOOP);
2127
2128 priv->slideshow_switch_timeout =
2129 g_settings_get_int (priv->fullscreen_settings,
2130 EOM_CONF_FULLSCREEN_SECONDS);
2131
2132 slideshow_set_timeout (window);
2133 }
2134
2135 upscale = g_settings_get_boolean (priv->fullscreen_settings,
2136 EOM_CONF_FULLSCREEN_UPSCALE);
2137
2138 eom_scroll_view_set_zoom_upscale (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (priv->view),
2139 upscale);
2140
2141 gtk_widget_grab_focus (priv->view);
2142
2143 eom_scroll_view_override_bg_color (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (window->priv->view),

2146 gtk_window_fullscreen (GTK_WINDOW (window));

2152 eom_window_update_slideshow_action (window);
2153 eom_window_update_fullscreen_action (window);
2154 eom_window_update_pause_slideshow_action (window);

2159{
2160 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
2161 GtkWidget *menubar;

2163 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
2164
2165 priv = window->priv;

2218eom_window_print (EomWindow *window)
2219{
2220 GtkWidget *dialog;

2222 GtkPrintOperation *print;

2224 GtkPageSetup *page_setup;

2228 eom_debug (DEBUG_PRINTING);
2229
2230 print_settings = eom_print_get_print_settings ();
2231
2232 /* Make sure the window stays valid while printing */
2233 g_object_ref (window);

2237 else
2238 page_setup = eom_print_get_page_setup ();

2240 print = eom_print_operation_new (window->priv->image,

2246 EOM_CONF_LOCKDOWN_CAN_SETUP_PAGE);

2249
2250 res = gtk_print_operation_run (print,
2251 GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_ACTION_PRINT_DIALOG,

2346static void
2347close_confirmation_dialog_response_handler (EomCloseConfirmationDialog *dlg,
2348 gint response_id,
2349 EomWindow *window)
2350{
2351 GList *selected_images;
2352 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
2353
2354 priv = window->priv;
2355
2356 switch (response_id)
2357 {
2358 case GTK_RESPONSE_YES:
2359 /* save selected images */
2360 selected_images = eom_close_confirmation_dialog_get_selected_images (dlg);
2361 if (eom_window_save_images (window, selected_images)) {
2362 g_signal_connect (priv->save_job, "finished",
2363 G_CALLBACK (eom_job_close_save_cb),
2364 window);
2365
2366 eom_job_queue_add_job (priv->save_job);
2367 }
2368
2369 break;
2370
2371 case GTK_RESPONSE_NO:
2372 /* dont save */
2373 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (window));
2374 break;
2375
2376 default:
2377 /* Cancel */
2378 gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (dlg));
2379 break;
2380 }
2381}

2383static gboolean
2384eom_window_unsaved_images_confirm (EomWindow *window)
2385{
2386 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
2387 gboolean disabled;
2388 GtkWidget *dialog;
2389 GList *list;
2390 EomImage *image;
2391 GtkTreeIter iter;
2392
2393 priv = window->priv;
2394
2395 disabled = g_settings_get_boolean(priv->ui_settings,
2396 EOM_CONF_UI_DISABLE_CLOSE_CONFIRMATION);
2397 disabled |= window->priv->save_disabled;
2398 if (disabled || !priv->store) {
2399 return FALSE;
2400 }
2401
2402 list = NULL;
2403 if (gtk_tree_model_get_iter_first (GTK_TREE_MODEL (priv->store), &iter)) {
2404 do {
2405 gtk_tree_model_get (GTK_TREE_MODEL (priv->store), &iter,
2406 EOM_LIST_STORE_EOM_IMAGE, &image,
2407 -1);
2408 if (!image)
2409 continue;
2410
2411 if (eom_image_is_modified (image)) {
2412 list = g_list_prepend (list, image);
2413 }
2414 } while (gtk_tree_model_iter_next (GTK_TREE_MODEL (priv->store), &iter));
2415 }
2416
2417 if (list) {
2418 list = g_list_reverse (list);
2419 dialog = eom_close_confirmation_dialog_new (GTK_WINDOW (window),
2420 list);
2421
2422 g_list_free (list);
2423 g_signal_connect (dialog, "response",
2424 G_CALLBACK (close_confirmation_dialog_response_handler),
2425 window);
2426 gtk_window_set_destroy_with_parent (GTK_WINDOW (dialog), TRUE);
2427
2428 gtk_widget_show (dialog);
2429 return TRUE;
2430
2431 }
2432 return FALSE;
2433}

2668 if (priv->mode != EOM_WINDOW_MODE_NORMAL &&
2669 priv->mode != EOM_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN) return;
2670
2671 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2672 visible = gtk_toggle_action_get_active (GTK_TOGGLE_ACTION (action));
2673 action_name = gtk_action_get_name (action);
2674 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2675
2676 if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (action_name, "ViewToolbar") == 0) {
2677 g_object_set (G_OBJECT (priv->toolbar), "visible", visible, NULL);
2678
2679 if (priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_NORMAL)
2680 g_settings_set_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_TOOLBAR, visible);
2681
2682 } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (action_name, "ViewStatusbar") == 0) {
2683 g_object_set (G_OBJECT (priv->statusbar), "visible", visible, NULL);
2684
2685 if (priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_NORMAL)
2686 g_settings_set_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_STATUSBAR, visible);
2687
2688 } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (action_name, "ViewImageCollection") == 0) {
2689 if (visible) {
2690 /* Make sure the focus widget is realized to
2691 * avoid warnings on keypress events */
2692 if (!gtk_widget_get_realized (window->priv->thumbview))
2693 gtk_widget_realize (window->priv->thumbview);
2694
2695 gtk_widget_show (priv->nav);
2696 gtk_widget_grab_focus (priv->thumbview);
2697 } else {
2698 /* Make sure the focus widget is realized to
2699 * avoid warnings on keypress events.
2700 * Don't do it during init phase or the view
2701 * will get a bogus allocation. */
2702 if (!gtk_widget_get_realized (priv->view)
2703 && priv->status == EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_NORMAL)
2704 gtk_widget_realize (priv->view);
2705
2706 gtk_widget_hide (priv->nav);
2707
2708 if (gtk_widget_get_realized (priv->view))
2709 gtk_widget_grab_focus (priv->view);
2710 }
2711 g_settings_set_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_IMAGE_COLLECTION, visible);
2712
2713 } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (action_name, "ViewSidebar") == 0) {
2714 if (visible) {
2715 gtk_widget_show (priv->sidebar);
2716 } else {
2717 gtk_widget_hide (priv->sidebar);
2718 }
2719 g_settings_set_boolean (priv->ui_settings, EOM_CONF_UI_SIDEBAR, visible);
2720 }
2721}

2752 error->message);
2753 g_error_free (error);
2754 error = NULL;
2755 }
2756
2757 g_object_unref (context);
2758 g_object_unref (app_info);

2857{

2859 gchar *filepath, *basename, *filename, *extension;
2860 GtkAction *action;
2861 GFile *source_file, *dest_file;
2862
2863 /* Create source GFile */
2864 basename = g_file_get_basename (job->images->data);
2865 filepath = g_build_filename (job->dest, basename, NULL);
2866 source_file = g_file_new_for_path (filepath);
2867 g_free (filepath);
2868
2869 /* Create destination GFile */
2870 extension = eom_util_filename_get_extension (basename);
2871 filename = g_strdup_printf ("%s.%s", EOM_WALLPAPER_FILENAME, extension);
2872 filepath = g_build_filename (job->dest, filename, NULL);
2873 dest_file = g_file_new_for_path (filepath);
2874 g_free (filename);

2879 NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
2880

2882 eom_window_set_wallpaper (window, filepath, basename);
2883 g_free (basename);
2884 g_free (filepath);

2886 gtk_statusbar_pop (GTK_STATUSBAR (window->priv->statusbar),
2887 window->priv->copy_file_cid);
2888 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2889 action = gtk_action_group_get_action (window->priv->actions_image,

2892 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
2893
2894 window->priv->copy_job = NULL;
2895
2896 g_object_unref (source_file);
2897 g_object_unref (dest_file);

2946static GFile*
2947eom_window_retrieve_save_as_file (EomWindow *window, EomImage *image)
2948{
2949 GtkWidget *dialog;
2950 GFile *save_file = NULL;
2951 GFile *last_dest_folder;
2952 gint response;
2953
2954 g_assert (image != NULL);
2955
2956 dialog = eom_file_chooser_new (GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ACTION_SAVE);
2957
2958 last_dest_folder = window->priv->last_save_as_folder;
2959
2960 if (last_dest_folder && g_file_query_exists (last_dest_folder, NULL)) {
2961 gtk_file_chooser_set_current_folder_file (GTK_FILE_CHOOSER (dialog), last_dest_folder, NULL);
2962 gtk_file_chooser_set_current_name (GTK_FILE_CHOOSER (dialog),
2963 eom_image_get_caption (image));
2964 } else {
2965 GFile *image_file;
2966
2967 image_file = eom_image_get_file (image);
2968 /* Setting the file will also navigate to its parent folder */
2969 gtk_file_chooser_set_file (GTK_FILE_CHOOSER (dialog),
2970 image_file, NULL);
2971 g_object_unref (image_file);
2972 }
2973
2974 response = gtk_dialog_run (GTK_DIALOG (dialog));
2975 gtk_widget_hide (dialog);
2976
2977 if (response == GTK_RESPONSE_OK) {
2978 save_file = gtk_file_chooser_get_file (GTK_FILE_CHOOSER (dialog));
2979 if (window->priv->last_save_as_folder)
2980 g_object_unref (window->priv->last_save_as_folder);
2981 window->priv->last_save_as_folder = g_file_get_parent (save_file);
2982 }
2983 gtk_widget_destroy (dialog);
2984

3291static int

3296 int response;
3297 int n_images;
3298 EomImage *image;
3299 static gboolean dontaskagain = FALSE;
3300 gboolean neverask = FALSE;

3313
3314 if (n_images == 1) {
3315 image = EOM_IMAGE (images->data);
3316 if (can_trash) {
3317 prompt = g_strdup_printf (_("Are you sure you want to move\n\"%s\" to the trash?"),
3318 eom_image_get_caption (image));
3319 } else {
3320 prompt = g_strdup_printf (_("A trash for \"%s\" couldn't be found. Do you want to remove "
3321 "this image permanently?"), eom_image_get_caption (image));
3322 }
3323 } else {
3324 if (can_trash) {
3325 prompt = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("Are you sure you want to move\n"
3326 "the %d selected image to the trash?",
3327 "Are you sure you want to move\n"
3328 "the %d selected images to the trash?", n_images), n_images);
3329 } else {
3330 prompt = g_strdup (_("Some of the selected images can't be moved to the trash "
3331 "and will be removed permanently. Are you sure you want "
3332 "to proceed?"));
3333 }
3334 }
3335
3336 dlg = gtk_message_dialog_new_with_markup (GTK_WINDOW (window),
3337 GTK_DIALOG_MODAL | GTK_DIALOG_DESTROY_WITH_PARENT,
3338 GTK_MESSAGE_WARNING,
3339 GTK_BUTTONS_NONE,
3340 "<span weight=\"bold\" size=\"larger\">%s</span>",
3341 prompt);
3342 g_free (prompt);
3343
3344 gtk_dialog_add_button (GTK_DIALOG (dlg), "gtk-cancel", GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL);
3345
3346 if (can_trash) {
3347 gtk_dialog_add_button (GTK_DIALOG (dlg), _("Move to _Trash"), GTK_RESPONSE_OK);
3348
3349 dontask_cbutton = gtk_check_button_new_with_mnemonic (_("_Do not ask again during this session"));
3350 gtk_toggle_button_set_active (GTK_TOGGLE_BUTTON (dontask_cbutton), FALSE);
3351
3352 gtk_box_pack_end (GTK_BOX (gtk_dialog_get_content_area (GTK_DIALOG (dlg))), dontask_cbutton, TRUE, TRUE, 0);
3353 } else {
3354 if (n_images == 1) {
3355 gtk_dialog_add_button (GTK_DIALOG (dlg), "gtk-delete", GTK_RESPONSE_OK);
3356 } else {
3357 gtk_dialog_add_button (GTK_DIALOG (dlg), "gtk-yes", GTK_RESPONSE_OK);
3358 }
3359 }
3360
3361 gtk_dialog_set_default_response (GTK_DIALOG (dlg), GTK_RESPONSE_OK);
3362 gtk_window_set_title (GTK_WINDOW (dlg), "");
3363 gtk_widget_show_all (dlg);
3364
3365 response = gtk_dialog_run (GTK_DIALOG (dlg));
3366
3367 /* Only update the property if the user has accepted */
3368 if (can_trash && response == GTK_RESPONSE_OK)
3369 dontaskagain = gtk_toggle_button_get_active (GTK_TOGGLE_BUTTON (dontask_cbutton));
3370
3371 /* The checkbutton is destroyed together with the dialog */
3372 gtk_widget_destroy (dlg);
3373
3374 return response;
3375}
3376
3377static gboolean
3378move_to_trash_real (EomImage *image, GError **error)
3379{
3380 GFile *file;
3381 GFileInfo *file_info;
3382 gboolean can_trash, result;
3383
3384 g_return_val_if_fail (EOM_IS_IMAGE (image), FALSE);
3385
3386 file = eom_image_get_file (image);
3387 file_info = g_file_query_info (file,
3388 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_ACCESS_CAN_TRASH,
3389 0, NULL, NULL);
3390 if (file_info == NULL) {
3391 g_set_error (error,
3392 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR,
3393 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR_TRASH_NOT_FOUND,
3394 _("Couldn't access trash."));
3395 return FALSE;
3396 }
3397
3398 can_trash = g_file_info_get_attribute_boolean (file_info,
3399 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_ACCESS_CAN_TRASH);
3400 g_object_unref (file_info);
3401 if (can_trash)
3402 {
3403 result = g_file_trash (file, NULL, NULL);
3404 if (result == FALSE) {
3405 g_set_error (error,
3406 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR,
3407 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR_TRASH_NOT_FOUND,
3408 _("Couldn't access trash."));
3409 }
3410 } else {
3411 result = g_file_delete (file, NULL, NULL);
3412 if (result == FALSE) {
3413 g_set_error (error,
3414 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR,
3415 EOM_WINDOW_ERROR_IO,
3416 _("Couldn't delete file"));
3417 }
3418 }
3419
3420 g_object_unref (file);
3421
3422 return result;
3423}

3451static void
3452eom_window_cmd_move_to_trash (GtkAction *action, gpointer user_data)
3453{
3454 GList *images;
3455 GList *it;
3456 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
3457 EomListStore *list;
3458 int pos;
3459 EomImage *img;
3460 EomWindow *window;
3461 int response;
3462 int n_images;
3463 gboolean success;
3464 gboolean can_trash;
3465 const gchar *action_name;
3466
3467 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (user_data));
3468
3469 window = EOM_WINDOW (user_data);
3470 priv = window->priv;
3471 list = priv->store;
3472
3473 n_images = eom_thumb_view_get_n_selected (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview));
3474
3475 if (n_images < 1) return;
3476
3477 /* save position of selected image after the deletion */
3478 images = eom_thumb_view_get_selected_images (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview));
3479
3480 g_assert (images != NULL);
3481
3482 /* HACK: eom_list_store_get_n_selected return list in reverse order */
3483 images = g_list_reverse (images);
3484
3485 can_trash = eom_window_all_images_trasheable (images);
3486
3487 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
3488 action_name = gtk_action_get_name (action);
3489 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
3490
3491 if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (action_name, "Delete") == 0 ||
3492 can_trash == FALSE) {
3493 response = show_move_to_trash_confirm_dialog (window, images, can_trash);
3494
3495 if (response != GTK_RESPONSE_OK) return;
3496 }
3497
3498 pos = eom_list_store_get_pos_by_image (list, EOM_IMAGE (images->data));
3499
3500 /* FIXME: make a nice progress dialog */
3501 /* Do the work actually. First try to delete the image from the disk. If this
3502 * is successful, remove it from the screen. Otherwise show error dialog.
3503 */
3504 for (it = images; it != NULL; it = it->next) {
3505 GError *error = NULL;
3506 EomImage *image;
3507
3508 image = EOM_IMAGE (it->data);
3509
3510 success = move_to_trash_real (image, &error);
3511
3512 if (success) {
3513 eom_list_store_remove_image (list, image);
3514 } else {
3515 char *header;
3516 GtkWidget *dlg;
3517
3518 header = g_strdup_printf (_("Error on deleting image %s"),
3519 eom_image_get_caption (image));
3520
3521 dlg = gtk_message_dialog_new (GTK_WINDOW (window),
3522 GTK_DIALOG_MODAL | GTK_DIALOG_DESTROY_WITH_PARENT,
3523 GTK_MESSAGE_ERROR,
3524 GTK_BUTTONS_OK,
3525 "%s", header);
3526
3527 gtk_message_dialog_format_secondary_text (GTK_MESSAGE_DIALOG (dlg),
3528 "%s", error->message);
3529
3530 gtk_dialog_run (GTK_DIALOG (dlg));
3531
3532 gtk_widget_destroy (dlg);
3533
3534 g_free (header);
3535 }
3536 }
3537
3538 /* free list */
3539 g_list_free_full (images, g_object_unref);
3540
3541 /* select image at previously saved position */
3542 pos = MIN (pos, eom_list_store_length (list) - 1);
3543
3544 if (pos >= 0) {
3545 img = eom_list_store_get_image_by_pos (list, pos);
3546
3547 eom_thumb_view_set_current_image (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview),
3548 img,
3549 TRUE);
3550
3551 if (img != NULL) {
3552 g_object_unref (img);
3553 }
3554 }
3555}

4021
4022static gint
4023sort_recents_mru (GtkRecentInfo *a, GtkRecentInfo *b)
4024{
4025 gboolean has_eom_a, has_eom_b;
4026
4027 /* We need to check this first as gtk_recent_info_get_application_info
4028 * will treat it as a non-fatal error when the GtkRecentInfo doesn't
4029 * have the application registered. */
4030 has_eom_a = gtk_recent_info_has_application (a,
4031 EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME);
4032 has_eom_b = gtk_recent_info_has_application (b,
4033 EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME);
4034 if (has_eom_a && has_eom_b) {
4035 time_t time_a, time_b;
4036
4037 /* These should not fail as we already checked that
4038 * the application is registered with the info objects */
4039 gtk_recent_info_get_application_info (a,
4040 EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME,
4041 NULL,
4042 NULL,
4043 &time_a);
4044 gtk_recent_info_get_application_info (b,
4045 EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME,
4046 NULL,
4047 NULL,
4048 &time_b);
4049
4050 return (time_b - time_a);
4051 } else if (has_eom_a) {
4052 return -1;
4053 } else if (has_eom_b) {
4054 return 1;
4055 }
4056
4057 return 0;
4058}

4060static void
4061eom_window_update_recent_files_menu (EomWindow *window)
4062{
4063 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
4064 GList *actions = NULL, *li = NULL, *items = NULL;
4065 guint count_recent = 0;
4066
4067 priv = window->priv;
4068
4069 if (priv->recent_menu_id != 0)
4070 gtk_ui_manager_remove_ui (priv->ui_mgr, priv->recent_menu_id);
4071
4072 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4073 actions = gtk_action_group_list_actions (priv->actions_recent);
4074
4075 for (li = actions; li != NULL; li = li->next) {
4076 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (li->data,
4077 eom_window_open_recent_cb,
4078 window);
4079
4080 gtk_action_group_remove_action (priv->actions_recent,
4081 GTK_ACTION (li->data));
4082 }
4083 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4084
4085 g_list_free (actions);
4086
4087 priv->recent_menu_id = gtk_ui_manager_new_merge_id (priv->ui_mgr);
4088 items = gtk_recent_manager_get_items (gtk_recent_manager_get_default());
4089 items = g_list_sort (items, (GCompareFunc) sort_recents_mru);
4090
4091 for (li = items; li != NULL && count_recent < EOM_RECENT_FILES_LIMIT; li = li->next) {
4092 gchar *action_name;
4093 gchar *label;
4094 gchar *tip;
4095 gchar **display_name;
4096 gchar *label_filename;
4097 GtkAction *action;
4098 GtkRecentInfo *info = li->data;
4099
4100 /* Sorting moves non-EOM files to the end of the list.
4101 * So no file of interest will follow if this test fails */
4102 if (!gtk_recent_info_has_application (info, EOM_RECENT_FILES_APP_NAME))
4103 break;
4104
4105 count_recent++;
4106
4107 action_name = g_strdup_printf ("recent-info-%d", count_recent);
4108 display_name = g_strsplit (gtk_recent_info_get_display_name (info), "_", -1);
4109 label_filename = g_strjoinv ("__", display_name);
4110 label = g_strdup_printf ("%s_%d. %s",
4111 (is_rtl ? "\xE2\x80\x8F" : ""), count_recent, label_filename);
4112 g_free (label_filename);
4113 g_strfreev (display_name);
4114
4115 tip = gtk_recent_info_get_uri_display (info);
4116
4117 /* This is a workaround for a bug (#351945) regarding
4118 * gtk_recent_info_get_uri_display() and remote URIs.
4119 * mate_vfs_format_uri_for_display is sufficient here
4120 * since the password gets stripped when adding the
4121 * file to the recently used list. */
4122 if (tip == NULL)
4123 tip = g_uri_unescape_string (gtk_recent_info_get_uri (info), NULL);
4124
4125 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4126 action = gtk_action_new (action_name, label, tip, NULL);
4127 gtk_action_set_always_show_image (action, TRUE);
4128 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4129
4130 g_object_set_data_full (G_OBJECT (action), "gtk-recent-info",
4131 gtk_recent_info_ref (info),
4132 (GDestroyNotify) gtk_recent_info_unref);
4133
4134 g_object_set (G_OBJECT (action), "icon-name", "image-x-generic", NULL);
4135
4136 g_signal_connect (action, "activate",
4137 G_CALLBACK (eom_window_open_recent_cb),
4138 window);
4139
4140 G_GNUC_BEGIN_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4141 gtk_action_group_add_action (priv->actions_recent, action);
4142 G_GNUC_END_IGNORE_DEPRECATIONS;
4143
4144 g_object_unref (action);
4145
4146 gtk_ui_manager_add_ui (priv->ui_mgr, priv->recent_menu_id,
4147 "/MainMenu/Image/RecentDocuments",
4148 action_name, action_name,
4149 GTK_UI_MANAGER_AUTO, FALSE);
4150
4151 g_free (action_name);
4152 g_free (label);
4153 g_free (tip);
4154 }
4155
4156 g_list_free_full (items, (GDestroyNotify) gtk_recent_info_unref);
4157}

4165static void
4166eom_window_drag_data_received (GtkWidget *widget,
4167 GdkDragContext *context,
4168 gint x, gint y,
4169 GtkSelectionData *selection_data,
4170 guint info, guint time)
4171{
4172 GSList *file_list;
4173 EomWindow *window;
4174 GdkAtom target;
4175 GtkWidget *src;
4176
4177 target = gtk_selection_data_get_target (selection_data);
4178
4179 if (!gtk_targets_include_uri (&target, 1))
4180 return;
4181
4182 /* if the request is from another process this will return NULL */
4183 src = gtk_drag_get_source_widget (context);
4184
4185 /* if the drag request originates from the current eom instance, ignore
4186 the request if the source window is the same as the dest window */
4187 if (src &&
4188 gtk_widget_get_toplevel (src) == gtk_widget_get_toplevel (widget))
4189 {
4190 gdk_drag_status (context, 0, time);
4191 return;
4192 }
4193
4194 if (gdk_drag_context_get_suggested_action (context) == GDK_ACTION_COPY) {
4195 window = EOM_WINDOW (widget);
4196
4197 file_list = eom_util_parse_uri_string_list_to_file_list ((const gchar *) gtk_selection_data_get_data (selection_data));
4198
4199 eom_window_open_file_list (window, file_list);
4200 }
4201}

4286
4287static GAppInfo *
4288get_appinfo_for_editor (EomWindow *window)
4289{
4290 /* We want this function to always return the same thing, not
4291 * just for performance reasons, but because if someone edits
4292 * GConf while eom is running, the application could get into an
4293 * inconsistent state. If the editor exists once, it gets added
4294 * to the "available" list of the EggToolbarsModel (for which
4295 * there is no API to remove it). If later the editor no longer
4296 * existed when constructing a new window, we'd be unable to
4297 * construct a GtkAction for the editor for that window, causing
4298 * assertion failures when viewing the "Edit Toolbars" dialog
4299 * (item is available, but can't find the GtkAction for it).
4300 *
4301 * By ensuring we keep the GAppInfo around, we avoid the
4302 * possibility of that situation occurring.
4303 */
4304 static GDesktopAppInfo *app_info = NULL;
4305 static gboolean initialised;
4306
4307 if (!initialised) {
4308 gchar *editor;
4309
4310 editor = g_settings_get_string (window->priv->ui_settings,
4311 EOM_CONF_UI_EXTERNAL_EDITOR);
4312
4313 if (editor != NULL) {
4314 app_info = g_desktop_app_info_new (editor);
4315 }
4316
4317 initialised = TRUE;
4318 g_free (editor);
4319 }
4320
4321 return (GAppInfo *) app_info;
4322}
4323
4324static void
4325eom_window_open_editor (GtkAction *action,
4326 EomWindow *window)
4327{
4328 GdkAppLaunchContext *context;
4329 GAppInfo *app_info;
4330 GList *files = NULL;
4331 GFile *file;
4332
4333 app_info = get_appinfo_for_editor (window);
4334
4335 if (app_info == NULL)
4336 return;
4337
4338 context = gdk_display_get_app_launch_context (
4339 gtk_widget_get_display (GTK_WIDGET (window)));
4340 gdk_app_launch_context_set_screen (context,
4341 gtk_widget_get_screen (GTK_WIDGET (window)));
4342 gdk_app_launch_context_set_icon (context,
4343 g_app_info_get_icon (app_info));
4344 gdk_app_launch_context_set_timestamp (context,
4345 gtk_get_current_event_time ());
4346
4347 file = eom_image_get_file (window->priv->image);
4348 files = g_list_append (files, file);
4349
4350 g_app_info_launch (app_info, files,
4351 G_APP_LAUNCH_CONTEXT (context), NULL);
4352
4353 g_list_free (files);
4354 g_object_unref (file);
4355 g_object_unref (context);
4356}

4928
4929static gint
4930eom_window_key_press (GtkWidget *widget, GdkEventKey *event)
4931{
4932 GtkContainer *tbcontainer = GTK_CONTAINER ((EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->toolbar));
4933 gint result = FALSE;
4934 gboolean handle_selection = FALSE;
4935
4936 switch (event->keyval) {
4937 case GDK_KEY_space:
4938 if (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) {
4939 handle_selection = TRUE;
4940 break;
4941 }
4942 case GDK_KEY_Return:
4943 if (gtk_container_get_focus_child (tbcontainer) == NULL) {
4944 /* Image properties dialog case */
4945 if (event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) {
4946 result = FALSE;
4947 break;
4948 }
4949
4950 if (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) {
4951 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
4952 } else {
4953 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
4954 }
4955 result = TRUE;
4956 }
4957 break;
4958 case GDK_KEY_p:
4959 case GDK_KEY_P:
4960 if (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN || EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW) {
4961 gboolean slideshow;
4962
4963 slideshow = EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW;
4964 eom_window_run_fullscreen (EOM_WINDOW (widget), !slideshow);
4965 }
4966 break;
4967 case GDK_KEY_Q:
4968 case GDK_KEY_q:
4969 case GDK_KEY_Escape:
4970 if (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN) {
4971 eom_window_stop_fullscreen (EOM_WINDOW (widget), FALSE);
4972 } else if (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW) {
4973 eom_window_stop_fullscreen (EOM_WINDOW (widget), TRUE);
4974 } else {
4975 eom_window_cmd_close_window (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
4976 return TRUE;
4977 }
4978 break;
4979 case GDK_KEY_Left:
4980 if (event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) {
4981 /* Alt+Left moves to previous image */
4982 if (is_rtl) { /* move to next in RTL mode */
4983 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
4984 } else {
4985 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
4986 }
4987 result = TRUE;
4988 break;
4989 } /* else fall-trough is intended */
4990 case GDK_KEY_Up:
4991 if (eom_scroll_view_scrollbars_visible (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view))) {
4992 /* break to let scrollview handle the key */
4993 break;
4994 }
4995 if (gtk_container_get_focus_child (tbcontainer) != NULL)
4996 break;
4997 if (!gtk_widget_get_visible (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->nav)) {
4998 if (is_rtl && event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Left) {
4999 /* handle RTL fall-through,
5000 * need to behave like GDK_Down then */
5001 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL,
5002 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5003 } else {
5004 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL,
5005 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5006 }
5007 result = TRUE;
5008 break;
5009 }
5010 case GDK_KEY_Right:
5011 if (event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) {
5012 /* Alt+Right moves to next image */
5013 if (is_rtl) { /* move to previous in RTL mode */
5014 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5015 } else {
5016 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL, EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5017 }
5018 result = TRUE;
5019 break;
5020 } /* else fall-trough is intended */
5021 case GDK_KEY_Down:
5022 if (eom_scroll_view_scrollbars_visible (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view))) {
5023 /* break to let scrollview handle the key */
5024 break;
5025 }
5026 if (gtk_container_get_focus_child (tbcontainer) != NULL)
5027 break;
5028 if (!gtk_widget_get_visible (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->nav)) {
5029 if (is_rtl && event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Right) {
5030 /* handle RTL fall-through,
5031 * need to behave like GDK_Up then */
5032 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL,
5033 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5034 } else {
5035 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL,
5036 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5037 }
5038 result = TRUE;
5039 break;
5040 }
5041 case GDK_KEY_Page_Up:
5042 if (!eom_scroll_view_scrollbars_visible (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view))) {
5043 if (!gtk_widget_get_visible (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->nav)) {
5044 /* If the iconview is not visible skip to the
5045 * previous image manually as it won't handle
5046 * the keypress then. */
5047 eom_window_cmd_go_prev (NULL,
5048 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5049 result = TRUE;
5050 } else
5051 handle_selection = TRUE;
5052 }
5053 break;
5054 case GDK_KEY_Page_Down:
5055 if (!eom_scroll_view_scrollbars_visible (EOM_SCROLL_VIEW (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view))) {
5056 if (!gtk_widget_get_visible (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->nav)) {
5057 /* If the iconview is not visible skip to the
5058 * next image manually as it won't handle
5059 * the keypress then. */
5060 eom_window_cmd_go_next (NULL,
5061 EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5062 result = TRUE;
5063 } else
5064 handle_selection = TRUE;
5065 }
5066 break;
5067 }
5068
5069 /* Update slideshow timeout */
5070 if (result && (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->mode == EOM_WINDOW_MODE_SLIDESHOW)) {
5071 slideshow_set_timeout (EOM_WINDOW (widget));
5072 }
5073
5074 if (handle_selection == TRUE && result == FALSE) {
5075 gtk_widget_grab_focus (GTK_WIDGET (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->thumbview));
5076
5077 result = gtk_widget_event (GTK_WIDGET (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->thumbview),
5078 (GdkEvent *) event);
5079 }
5080
5081 /* If the focus is not in the toolbar and we still haven't handled the
5082 event, give the scrollview a chance to do it. */
5083 if (!gtk_container_get_focus_child (tbcontainer) && result == FALSE &&
5084 gtk_widget_get_realized (GTK_WIDGET (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view))) {
5085 result = gtk_widget_event (GTK_WIDGET (EOM_WINDOW (widget)->priv->view),
5086 (GdkEvent *) event);
5087 }
5088
5089 if (result == FALSE && GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (eom_window_parent_class)->key_press_event) {
5090 result = (* GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (eom_window_parent_class)->key_press_event) (widget, event);
5091 }
5092
5093 return result;
5094}
5095
5096static gint
5097eom_window_button_press (GtkWidget *widget, GdkEventButton *event)
5098{
5099 EomWindow *window = EOM_WINDOW (widget);
5100 gint result = FALSE;
5101
5102 /* We currently can't tell whether the old button codes (6, 7) are
5103 * still in use. So we keep them in addition to the new ones (8, 9)
5104 */
5105 if (event->type == GDK_BUTTON_PRESS) {
5106 switch (event->button) {
5107 case 6:
5108 case 8:
5109 eom_thumb_view_select_single (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (window->priv->thumbview),
5110 EOM_THUMB_VIEW_SELECT_LEFT);
5111 result = TRUE;
5112 break;
5113 case 7:
5114 case 9:
5115 eom_thumb_view_select_single (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (window->priv->thumbview),

5386static void
5387eom_job_model_cb (EomJobModel *job, gpointer data)
5388{
5389 EomWindow *window;
5390 EomWindowPrivate *priv;
5391 gint n_images;
5392
5393 eom_debug (DEBUG_WINDOW);
5394
5395#ifdef HAVE_EXIF
5396 int i;
5397 EomImage *image;
5398#endif
5399
5400 g_return_if_fail (EOM_IS_WINDOW (data));
5401
5402 window = EOM_WINDOW (data);
5403 priv = window->priv;
5404
5405 if (priv->store != NULL) {
5406 g_object_unref (priv->store);
5407 priv->store = NULL;
5408 }
5409
5410 priv->store = g_object_ref (job->store);
5411
5412 n_images = eom_list_store_length (EOM_LIST_STORE (priv->store));
5413
5414#ifdef HAVE_EXIF
5415 if (g_settings_get_boolean (priv->view_settings, EOM_CONF_VIEW_AUTOROTATE)) {
5416 for (i = 0; i < n_images; i++) {
5417 image = eom_list_store_get_image_by_pos (priv->store, i);
5418 eom_image_autorotate (image);
5419 g_object_unref (image);
5420 }
5421 }
5422#endif
5423
5424 eom_thumb_view_set_model (EOM_THUMB_VIEW (priv->thumbview), priv->store);
5425
5426 g_signal_connect (priv->store, "row-inserted",
5427 G_CALLBACK (eom_window_list_store_image_added),
5428 window);
5429
5430 g_signal_connect (priv->store, "row-deleted",
5431 G_CALLBACK (eom_window_list_store_image_removed),
5432 window);
5433
5434 if (n_images == 0) {
5435 gint n_files;
5436
5437 priv->status = EOM_WINDOW_STATUS_NORMAL;
5438 update_action_groups_state (window);
5439
5440 n_files = g_slist_length (priv->file_list);
5441
5442 if (n_files > 0) {
5443 GtkWidget *message_area;
5444 GFile *file = NULL;
5445
5446 if (n_files == 1) {
5447 file = (GFile *) priv->file_list->data;
5448 }
5449
5450 message_area = eom_no_images_error_message_area_new (file);
5451
5452 eom_window_set_message_area (window, message_area);
5453
5454 gtk_widget_show (message_area);
5455 }
5456
5457 g_signal_emit (window, signals[SIGNAL_PREPARED], 0);
5458 }
5459}
